## Title
[Specific — 3 to 10 words. NOT "Team Meeting" or "Weekly Sync" — name the actual topics.]

## Summary
4-6 sentences: purpose, key decisions, critical blockers, financial highlights, urgent items.

## Detailed Notes
Narrative walkthrough in the order topics came up — reasoning, trade-offs, alternatives, pushback, open questions behind each discussion. Attribute to named participants. Do not duplicate the structured lists below verbatim.

## Decisions
For each: **Decision** / **Rationale** / **Options considered** / **Approved by** / **Scope or constraints**. Populate `decisions`.

## Financial Review
Cloud spend & budget (actuals vs. forecast, anomalies), cost optimization / ROI, P&L or revenue impact. Omit this heading entirely if finance was not discussed.

## Blockers, Risks & Escalations
For each: what, who is impacted, severity, who owns resolution, escalation path.

### Operational
Outages, access, tooling, on-call burden, incident response gaps.

### Organizational
Cross-team dependencies, approval bottlenecks, staffing, unclear priorities, process friction.

### Infrastructure / Physical
Hardware, network, data center, capacity, connectivity.

### Strategic / Roadmap
Product direction, feature priority conflicts, tech debt, migration timeline risks, pending vendor decisions.

### Cross-Team Dependencies
For each: what / from which team / committed date / status / escalation path.

## Strategic & Roadmap Updates
OKR progress, roadmap changes, leadership direction, market context, build-vs-buy, migration strategy.

## Technology Decisions & Architecture
ADR-worthy items, tech choices, tech debt priorities, platform/tooling changes, security/compliance.

